            <div>

                <ol>
                    <li>
                        Cook the rice in a pan of boiling salted water according to the packet instructions, then drain and refresh under cold water,
                        leaving it in the colander.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        At the same time, poach the fish in a large pan of simmering salted water on a medium heat for 10 minutes,then carefully
                        remove with a slotted spoon. Turn the heat up under the poaching water and bring back to a good simmer.

                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Meahwhile, peel the onions and finely slice with the red chilli (deseed if you like) and coriander stalks. Peel and finely
                        chop the garlic and ginger. Place it all in a large frying pan on a medium heat with 1 tablespoon
                        of oil and the butter, and cook for 10 minutes, or until soft but not coloured, stirring occasionally.
                    </li>
